	(924, 'D-11/2023/86', 'Mukesh Jain', NULL, 'Mukesh Jain', 'mukesh21357@yahoo.co.in', '8279864312', 'India', 'MEDIUM', NULL, 'I', NULL, '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<header style="background-image: url(\'../../img/header-stirp.png\'); background-position: top center; background-repeat: no-repeat; border-bottom: 2px solid #005B89; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; padding: 55px 20px 30px 20px; align-items: center; background-size: 100%;"><img style="width: 200px;" src="../../img/logo-investor-summit.png" alt="Global Investor Summit 2023"> <img style="width: 100px; margin-left: 430px;" src="../../img/logo-uttarakhand.png" alt="Government of Uttarakhand"></header>\r\n<div class="mou-box">\r\n<p style="margin-left: 560px; margin-top: 5px;">MoU No : D-11/2023/86 <!-- <p style="margin-left:620px;width:20%; height: 1px; background-color: #000;"></p> --> <!-- <input type="text" class="form-input"> --></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1 style="font-size: 18px; font-weight: 900; text-align: center; margin: 30px 0 20px; line-height: 30px; font-family: \'Montserrat\', sans-serif;"><strong>MEMORANDUM</strong><br><strong>OF</strong><br><strong>UNDERSTANDING (MoU)</strong></h1>\r\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 900; line-height: 14px; text-align: center; font-family: \'Montserrat\', sans-serif;">This MoU is entered on 20<sup style="vertical-align: super;">th</sup> day of November 2023</p>\r\n<h2 style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; margin: 21px 0 29px; text-align: center;">Between</h2>\r\n<table style="width: 100%; margin-left: 70px;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="width: 40%;">\r\n<table style="width: 300px; height: 300px; border-radius: 5px; background-color: #ffffff; display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; padding: 20px;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 24px;">Mukesh Jain</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style="width: 10%;">\r\n<table style="display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; padding: 20px;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2 style="font-size: 16px; margin: 0;">&amp;</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style="width: 40%;">\r\n<table style="width: 300px; height: 300px; border-radius: 5px; background-color: #ffffff; display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; padding: 20px;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2 style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; text-align: center; height: 50px; min-height: 40px;">Government of Uttarakhand</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h2 style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; margin: 41px 0 39px; text-align: center;">wherein</h2>\r\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; margin-left: 50px;">M/s Mukesh Jain, wishes to establish the following project(s) in Uttarakhand-</p>\r\n<table style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; background-color: #ffffff; text-align: left; margin: 40px 0; border: 1px solid #000000; margin-left: 50px; margin-right: 50px;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style="border: 1px solid #000000;">\r\n<th style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; padding: 10px 5px; border: 1px solid #000000;">Project Brief</th>\r\n<th style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; padding: 10px 5px; border: 1px solid #000000;">Location</th>\r\n<th style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; padding: 10px 5px; border: 1px solid #000000;">Minimum Investment (in INR Crore)</th>\r\n<th style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; padding: 10px 5px; border: 1px solid #000000;">Direct Employment (in number)</th>\r\n<th style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; padding: 10px 5px; border: 1px solid #000000;">Expected date of commencement</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; padding: 10px 5px; border: 1px solid #000000;">COMPRESSED BIOGAS PLANTS IN STATE OF UTTARAKHAND</td>\r\n<td style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; padding: 10px 5px; border: 1px solid #000000;">DEHRADUN, HALDWANI, RUDRAPUR</td>\r\n<td style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; padding: 10px 5px; border: 1px solid #000000;">100</td>\r\n<td style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; padding: 10px 5px; border: 1px solid #000000;">&gt;200</td>\r\n<td style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; padding: 10px 5px; border: 1px solid #000000;">DECEMBER 2024</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 2pt; margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; padding-left: 40px;"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt;">We hereby indicate our intent to set up Compressed Biogas Plants in the State of Uttarakhand.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; padding-left: 40px;"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; padding-left: 40px;"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt;">These plants will use agricultural feedstock (press mud from sugar mills) <strong>to produce clean and renewable biogas that can replace the use of fossil fueled natural gas thus providing a cleaner energy solution.</strong> Note that these plant could also use other organic waste such as municipal solid waste, paddy straw, napier grass however for the start we will focus on utilizing the press mud from sugar mills as feedback. </span><span style="font-size: 10.0pt;">The plant will also<strong> produce organic fertilizer that can be used as a replacement of chemical fertilizer providing a more sustainable way of agriculture for our famers in the State of Uttarakhand.</strong> </span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; padding-left: 40px;"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; padding-left: 40px;"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt;">The proposed plant plans to use press mud which is a compressed sugar industry waste produced during filtration of cane juice. This plant can also use bagasse, the other by product from a sugar mill. Through our preliminary research, we believe there are a total of 8 large scale sugar mills in Uttarakhand, more than half state owned, with a total crushing capacity of 37,500t on a daily basis. 4 of the plants are around Rudrapur, Haldwani region, 3 of the plants around Roorkee and 1 near Dehradun. </span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; padding-left: 40px;"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; padding-left: 40px;"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt;">Our proposal is to set up <strong>1 large scale biogas plant around Doiwala, Dehradun</strong> region aiming to supply renewable gas via city gas distribution (CGD) lines in Dehradun and another <strong>large-scale biogas plant in Haldwani, Rudrapur</strong> region. The output of each plant would be 10tonne of CBG/day and ~150tonne of solid and liquid digestate on a daily basis. For the plants we are looking to <strong>source 1.5lakh tonne of press mud annually</strong> from multiple sugar mills in Uttarakhand for a 15&ndash;20-year tenure. We are also evaluating to use bagasse, if surplus available we would also be interested in long term offtake of bagasse as well. </span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; margin-top: 0in; mso-margin-bottom-alt: 8.0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: 0in; mso-add-space: auto; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 8pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; padding-left: 40px;"><span style="font-size: 10.0pt;">Since this will be a high capex investment of around ~100cr and will directly and indirectly employ more than 200 people, we humbly seek Uttarakhand State&rsquo;s support for policies that are in line with other state and national led policies for the CBG sector. Few example of requests are:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="margin-bottom: 2pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; padding-left: 80px;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">1.<span style="font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt;">Land requirement of 15-20 acres: Subsidized land for the plants near to the major cities in Uttarakhand in proximity to the city gas distribution pipelines; </span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="margin-bottom: 2pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; padding-left: 80px;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">2.<span style="font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt;">Capex subsidy for setting up these CBG plants;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="margin-bottom: 2pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; padding-left: 80px;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">3.<span style="font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt;">Any waivers on stamp duty, electricity duties etc.;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="margin-bottom: 2pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; padding-left: 80px;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">4.<span style="font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt;">Support on road connectivity and connections to the city gas distribution pipelines</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="margin-bottom: 2pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; padding-left: 80px;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">5.<span style="font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt;">Support in securing long term agricultural feedstock.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; line-height: 24px; ;margin-left: 50px; margin-left: 50px;">Government of Uttarakhand would facilitate the investor to obtain all necessary approvals/clearances for commencement of the project. The MoU shall remain valid for a period of 12 months.</p>\r\n<p><br><br><br></p>\r\n<table style="width: 100%; ;margin-left: 50px; margin-left: 50px;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="width: 50%;">\r\n<table style="width: 300px; height: 300px; border-radius: 5px; display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; padding: 20px;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<div><!-- <input type="text" style="border:none;border-bottom:2px solid #000000;background-color:transparent;font-size:18px;font-weight:600;width:250px;"> -->\r\n<p style="margin-left: 3px; width: 106%; height: 1px; background-color: #000;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; line-height: 24px; margin-top: 20px;">On behalf of<br>Mukesh Jain<br><br></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style="width: 50%;">\r\n<table style="width: 300px; height: 300px; border-radius: 5px; display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; padding: 20px;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<div><!-- <input type="text" style="border:none;border-bottom:2px solid #000000;background-color:transparent;font-size:18px;font-weight:600;width:300px"> -->\r\n<p style="margin-left: 3px; width: 106%; height: 1px; background-color: #000;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="text-left" style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; line-height: 24px; margin-top: 20px;">On behalf of <br>Government of Uttarakhand,</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<footer style="background-image: url(\'../../img/footer-stirp.png\'); background-position: top center; background-repeat: no-repeat; height: 60px; background-size: 100%;"></footer>', 'SUBJECT: PROPOSAL TO SET UP COMPRESSED BIOGAS (CBG) PLANTS IN UTTARAKHAND.\r\n\r\nTo,\r\nChairman of Global Investor Summit 2023 of Uttarakhand\r\n\r\nRespected Sir,\r\n\r\nWe hereby indicate our intent to set up Compressed Biogas Plants in the State of Uttarakhand.\r\n\r\nThese plants will use agricultural feedstock (press mud from sugar mills) to produce clean and renewable biogas that can replace the use of fossil fueled natural gas thus providing a cleaner energy solution. Note that these plant could also use other organic waste such as municipal solid waste, paddy straw, napier grass however for the start we will focus on utilizing the press mud from sugar mills as feedback. \r\n\r\nThe plant will also produce organic fertilizer that can be used as a replacement of chemical fertilizer providing a more sustainable way of agriculture for our famers in the State of Uttarakhand. \r\n\r\nThe proposed plant plans to use press mud which is a compressed sugar industry waste produced during filtration of cane juice. This plant can also use bagasse, the other by product from a sugar mill. Through our preliminary research, we believe there are a total of 8 large scale sugar mills in Uttarakhand, more than half state owned, with a total crushing capacity of 37,500t on a daily basis. 4 of the plants are around Rudrapur, Haldwani region, 3 of the plants around Roorkee and 1 near Dehradun. \r\n\r\nOur proposal is to set up 1 large scale biogas plant around Doiwala, Dehradun region aiming to supply renewable gas via city gas distribution (CGD) lines in Dehradun and another large-scale biogas plant in Haldwani, Rudrapur region. The output of each plant would be 10tonne of CBG/day and ~150tonne of solid and liquid digestate on a daily basis. For the plants we are looking to source 1.5lakh tonne of press mud annually from multiple sugar mills in Uttarakhand for a 15–20-year tenure. We are also evaluating to use bagasse, if surplus available we would also be interested in long term offtake of bagasse as well. \r\n\r\nSince this will be a high capex investment of around ~100cr and will directly and indirectly employ more than 200 people, we humbly seek Uttarakhand State’s support for policies that are in line with other state and national led policies for the CBG sector. Few requests are:\r\n1.	Land requirement of 15-20 acres: Subsidized land for the plants near to the major cities in Uttarakhand in proximity to the city gas distribution pipelines; \r\n2.	Capex subsidy for setting up these CBG plants;\r\n3.	Any waivers on stamp duty, electricity duties etc.;\r\n4.	Support on road connectivity and connections to the city gas distribution pipelines\r\n5.	Support in securing long term agricultural feedstock. \r\n6.	We attach a link to Uttar Pradesh’s recent policies on CBG: BIO-ENERGY ENTERPRISES PROMOTION PROGRAMME 2022  |  Official Website of Invest UP, Government of Uttar Pradesh, India. \r\n\r\nWe will be more than happy to provide further details on the project. \r\n\r\nWarm Regards,\r\n\r\nMukesh Jain\r\nVice President (Retired) Oil & Gas Division, Reliance Industries Ltd\r\nChief Operating Officer (Retired), Oil & Gas Division, Essar Oil Ltd ', NULL, 1000000000, 'Individual', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'D', 'S', NULL, NULL, NULL, 824, 'SUBMITTED', NULL, 'N', 'N', 'Y', '2023-11-20 15:55:00', NULL, 'I', NULL, 824, 'N', 'N', NULL, NULL, 'MoU-UKGIS-0002', NULL, '2023-11-20 10:37:07', NULL, '2023-11-20 10:25:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'N', NULL, NULL, NULL),
