	(950, 'E-11/2023/284', 'H Two IEnterprises', NULL, 'Siddharth M Hemmadi', 'sh@h2-industries.com', '9966033333', 'India', 'MEDIUM', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'H2-Enterprises’ Inc, is a holding company in the business of Hydrogen Generation and Energy Storage solutions, headquartered in New York City, United States of America. Founded by me, Mr. Michael Stusch, in the year 2010, the business focusses on developing technologies that generate, store, transport and release clean Hydrogen in a safe, reliable, and economic way.\r\n\r\nAt present H2-Enterprises is commercializing its technology by developing projects in more than twenty countries, collaborating with leading suppliers and consultants worldwide. For being closer to potential markets and partners in the region, we have established H2-Investments LLC in Dubai/ U.A.E., a 100% subsidiary of H2- Enterprises, looking after the Middle East and South Asia. To learn more about how H2- Enterprises is changing the renewable energy landscape, please visit (https://h2-enterprises.com/en).\r\n\r\n\r\nProtecting our environment involves significant challenges. Reducing the carbon footprint of energy production and the amount of waste we produce as a society are two of them. H2-Investments has developed a revolutionary solution to create and capture clean hydrogen and CO2 on utility scale level, using organic waste as feedstock for its hydrogen production. Both products, produced 100% CO2-emission-free will be sold to the market. More and more countries and major industries globally are recognizing that one of the most promising routes to a zero-carbon future is the production and use of clean, CO2-emission-free hydrogen. However, creating clean hydrogen has historically proven economically challenging.\r\n\r\nH2-Investments has developed a process to create large amounts of clean hydrogen from organic and plastic waste at competitive costs. The so produced hydrogen is being transported and stored, using LOHC (Liquid Organic Hydrogen Carriers), another H2-Investments technology, releasing Hydrogen on demand for use in various industrial, commercial or transportation applications.\r\n\r\nH2-Investments to develop US $1.4 billion waste-to-hydrogen plant in Egypt - world’s first and largest on this scale\r\nIn conjunction with COP27 (in 2022) preliminary approval has been granted to H2-Enterprises by the General Authority of Suez Canal Economic Zone (SC°Zone) for the development of a Waste-to-Hydrogen power plant in East Port-Said/ Egypt, which will be the first project of its type in the world.\r\n\r\n \r\n \r\nH2-Investments LLC.\r\nBay Square, Building 7, 6th Floor\r\n \r\nE-Mail:\r\ninfo@h2.enterprises\r\n \r\nBank details\r\nNBQ Dubai Main [USD]\r\n \r\nLicence number: 1085088\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\nThe hydrogen plant will be fed with 2 million tons of organic waste and non-recyclable plastic per year. The Suez Canal Project will produce 300,000 tons of clean hydrogen per year at less than half the levelized cost of current clean hydrogen production technologies, taking the cost even lower than current levels for low-carbon and grey hydrogen production.\r\n\r\n\r\nH2-Investments to develop US $1.4 billion waste-to-hydrogen plant in Oman\r\nH2-Investments and Public Establishment for Industrial Estates – Madayan have signed a memorandum of understanding (MOU) to develop a waste-to-hydrogen plant in conjunction with PV solar power plants with base- load capacity in the Sultanate of Oman. The proposed US $1.4 billion facility will be built on a 200,000m2 coastal site. The facility will initially convert up to one million tons of municipal solid waste each year sourced from waste management operators and mined from existing landfills but has the capacity to expand to manage up to four million tons of waste. The planned project for Oman will make a substantial contribution to the country’s waste management strategy and demonstrates how fighting climate change and enhancing environmental protection can go hand in hand and benefit all stakeholders.\r\n\r\n\r\nIn this context, we, H2-Investments LLC are expressing our keen interest in developing Waste-to-Hydrogen plants in India, including in the State of Uttarakhand, to produce clean Hydrogen, which would not just provide new opportunities for modernizing the waste management sector and re-developing existing landfills but also making the State ready to become a globally recognized user and exporter of clean Hydrogen.\r\n\r\n\r\nWe gather that multiple districts generate large amounts of Municipal and Plastic waste in Uttarakhand and that sufficient access to water is available, which could be tapped to produce clean Hydrogen. Our plant capacities start from an input feedstock of 350 tons of waste per day and upwards producing close to 20,000 tons of clean hydrogen per annum.\r\n\r\n\r\nIn this context, our Business partner for India, Mr. Siddharth Hemmadi, Director of Parinishtaa Eco Solutions\r\n(P) Ltd would like to make a detailed presentation to your good self and further explore the possibility of setting up Waste-to-Hydrogen plants in Uttarakhand.\r\n\r\nWe have enclosed a profile of our Company as well as a Project information sheet which has information on the various capacities of plants, we could build along with all other necessary information including the output of Clean Hydrogen generation from Waste.\r\n\r\nI would like to thank you for your time and look forward to working with the Government of Uttarakhand.\r\n', NULL, 24000000000, 'Organization', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'E', 'S', NULL, NULL, NULL, 838, 'SUBMITTED', NULL, 'N', 'N', 'Y', '2023-11-23 12:56:25', NULL, 'I', NULL, 838, 'N', 'N', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-11-23 07:26:25', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'N', NULL, NULL, NULL),
