	(956, 'D-11/2023/95', 'Healo Medicine Private Limited', NULL, 'Healo Medicine Private Limited', 'ajit.yadav.associates@gmail.com', '9810271349', 'India', 'MEDIUM', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'We propose to set up 40-bedded Cancer Care Hospital at Dehradun. Unique feature of the proposed hospital will be set up by worlds leading cancer surgeons who will deliver best-in-class cancer treatment leveraging traditional indian science of Ayurveda as complimentary therapies and medicine for overall well being of patients.\r\nProject Outlay: Rs 70 cr.\r\n\r\nProject Proposal is appended below.\r\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nSuper Speciality Cancer Care Hospital, Dehradun\r\n\r\nA Hospital – first of its kind- which will offer holistic cancer treatment by renowned global cancer surgeons supported by Ayurvedic therapies for overall well being – a path breaking approach in sync with State Govt’s AYUSH Policy,2023 and Prime Minister’s vision of “New India” , a “Healthy India” where modern cancer treatment works in conjunction with traditional Indian system of Ayurveda medicines and therapies for overall well being of patients\r\n\r\nProject Outlay Rs 68 -70 Cr. ( Over a period 3 years) \r\n\r\nProposal By:\r\n\r\n1.	Dr Kavita Singh M.B.B.S, M.D., FRCOG\r\n	Presently Consultant Surgical Oncologist, Pan-Birmingham Gynaecological Cancer Centre, 	Birmingham, United Kingdom;\r\n	Program Director for Subspecialty training;\r\n	Associate Professor, Cancer Institute. University of Birmingham, England; and\r\n	Visiting surgeon- Max Hospital  Dehradun/Delhi       and other leading hospitals in  Kolkata, 	Gurgaon, Chandigarh and Pune. \r\n	 And \r\n2.	Ajit Yadav\r\nFormerly Board of Directors , PepsiCo, Hindustan Unilever, Vedanta Group; Independent Director;\r\nFormerly IAS(Allied) Services.\r\nDirector, Healo Medicine Private Limited.\r\n\r\nRes:   Noor Bagh,\r\n11, Purkul Gaon, Dehradun-248009\r\nTel; 9810271349\r\nEmails; ajit.yadav.associates@gmail.com; dockavitasing@yahoo.co.uk\r\n\r\n\r\nBackground\r\n\r\nIncidence of cancer is increasing world over. Cancer as a disease is growing at an alarming rate in India. Cancer cases in India are projected to go up from 14.6 lakhs in 2022 to 15.7 lakhs in 2025 as per reported data. Actual number could well be higher . \r\n\r\nUttarakhand is no exception. As per govt data , Uttarakhand has seen 4-5% growth in cancer patients in the last 3 years. Total number of reported cases were 10,932 in 2018 which grew to 11216 in 2019 and 11482 in 2020. Actual number of detected case could well be significantly higher. Number of deaths  due to cancer has also seen high growth in the last few years. at. \r\n\r\nUnfortunately, medical facilities for handling rising cancer incidences, are majorly lacking and particularly so in Uttarakhand.   Survival outcome from all cancers centres in Indian subcontinent is quite low. Currently the infrastructure facilities, availability of cancer care, developments and provision of all medical advancements  in cancer care is sparse in Uttarakhand.\r\n\r\n So far cancer treatments in Uttarakhand  are very fragmented and often delivered via general hospitals without adequate   focus on research driven, evidence based delivery of cancer treatments. This generic delivery of cancer care does not always match the standard of care which can be achieved by a dedicated cancer hospital.  There is no dedicated cancer hospital in Dehradun and in entire state of Uttarakhand.\r\n\r\nMedical science in cancer treatments is  rapidly evolving and requires a multidisciplinary input/approach from dedicated trained medical professionals . Cancer treatments encompass a range of wide treatments looking at holistic provision of cancer care ranging from surgical, chemotherapy, radiotherapy, diagnostics, palliative care/ end of life care, screening and follow ups. A dedicated institution aimed towards provision of all aspects of cancer care will be a big step towards improving cancer care in Uttarakhand.\r\n\r\nSo far, it is not uncommon for cancer patients from Uttarakhand,  to travel long distances to avail appropriate cancer treatment. It is not only the patient but the whole family goes through their own traumatic experience which has an immense social and economic impact.\r\n\r\nCancer is a serious diagnosis and survival is dependent upon the quality of treatment and care  provided at their initial diagnosis. It is therefore an opportune time to bring high quality cancer services to the door steps for patients of Uttarakhand by building a dedicated cancer hospital in Dehradun. \r\n\r\nOur Aim : \r\n\r\nOur goal is to set up an integrated 40 -bedded cancer care hospital which will be first of its kind in India,  that combines modern medicine with Ayurveda medicine treatment and  will be based on holistic approach for treating cancer by  creating a cohesive space that accommodates and incorporates benefits  of modern sciences in conjunction with ancient Indian Ayurvedic science. \r\n\r\nThe proposed Hospital will promote collaboration between traditional and modern practitioners to enhance patient care and maximise the benefits for improving outcomes and quality of life for cancer patients in Uttarakhand. This active conjoint delivery of care will be exemplary as will be the first of its kind in India and will be delivered by  world experts with experience of working in United Kingdom over 30years, USA, France and India  along with senior successful expert Ayurvedic clinicians.\r\n\r\nThe proposed Hospital will be designed in such a manner that it not only prioritizes patient centric  care, it promotes synergy between modern medicine and Ayurveda while ensuring a supportive and uplifting environment for patients and healthcare providers alike.\r\n\r\nHospital’s Objectives :\r\n\r\n•	To improve outcome of cancer treatments in Uttarakhand in terms of survivals and reduced side-effects of modern medicine treatments like surgery/chemotherapy and radiotherapy.\r\n•	To ease the treatment journey of cancer patients by  giving best-in-class modern science based cancer treatment through renowned oncology surgeons and medical professionals who have established a name for themselves in some of the best hospitals in western countries as mentioned above. This service will be supported by incorporating complementary medicine like Ayurveda and its therapies for cancer care , yoga, pranayama, meditation, cosmic healing and naturopathy and nutrition at the proposed Centre.\r\n•	Holistic approach to physical, psychological, emotional and mental well- being of cancer patients and their families.\r\n•	Incorporate healing gardens and green spaces to promote well-being and provide a tranquil environment for patients.\r\n•	Implement state-of-the-art medical technology for diagnosis and treatment. Integrate information systems that allow seamless communication between allopathic  and Ayurvedic practitioners ..\r\n•	Include a wellness centre offering yoga, meditation, and other holistic therapies complementing cancer treatments.\r\n•	Establish a nutrition centre focusing on Ayurvedic dietary principles alongside conventional nutritional guidance.\r\n•	Create a supportive environment for emotional and psychological well-being of cancer patients and their caregivers\r\n•	Integrate outdoor spaces or healing gardens for relaxation and a connection to nature. Provide areas for cancer patients to reflect and find solace\r\n\r\nBy combining these elements, we will  create a boutique  cancer care hospital that prioritizes patient comfort, supports comprehensive care, holistic healing and facilitates collaboration between modern medicine  and Ayurveda and will be a beacon for others cancer delivery providers to follow.\r\n\r\nProposal\r\n\r\n We propose  to set up a  40-bedded integrated  Cancer Care Centre at Dehradun. The Centre will offer extensive and complex surgery, chemotherapy and radiotherapy treatments by renowned oncology surgeons and clinical experts. The Centre will have  best-in-class fully equipped Operation Theatres and other equipments to administer chemotherapy and radiology treatment with other support services. \r\n\r\nThe unique feature of this Centre will be that aforesaid services will be made available together with research based Ayurvedic medicines for a holistic treatment including Nutrition, meditation, yoga & pranayama, cosmic healing as an  integral part of cancer treatment in conjunction with modern cancer therapies as above. . The Centre will deploy  valuable tools to manage stress, enhance coping mechanisms, and improve patients  overall quality of life during and after cancer treatment. \r\n\r\nThe Centre will have Designated quiet and comfortable spaces within the hospital/Centre  for meditation sessions and  outdoor areas or spaces with natural light for a serene environment which will enhance and promote their healing and makes available  a place of solace for  healing.   \r\n\r\nThe proposed Hospital will generate employment for about 100 people including medical , para medical , nurses and other staff in the State.\r\n\r\nThe Centre will offer  comprehensive treatment packages for regional, national and international patients. Dehradun is ideally suited to become medical destination of choice for patients from other cities of India and overseas , to avail of world class cancer treatment.  \r\n\r\nA New Approach \r\n\r\nThe proposed Cancer Centre will  foster collaboration between medical oncology team and Ayurvedic practitioners  to create integrated treatment plans. Individualized Ayurvedic assessments will be carried out for all patients, considering their dosha (constitution) and overall health status.\r\n\r\nAyurvedic herbal formulations will be collaborated which are known for their potential benefits in cancer support, such as Ashwagandha, Turmeric, and Tulsi and others. Provide personalized dietary recommendations based on Ayurvedic principles to support patients during and after cancer treatment. Offer specific Panchakarma therapies, tailored to individual patient needs, to detoxify and rejuvenate the body. Integrate Ayurvedic yoga and meditation programs into the overall cancer care plan to support mental and emotional well-being.\r\n\r\nWe will guide patients in Ayurvedic lifestyle modifications, including daily routines (Dinacharya) and seasonal practices (Ritucharya). Incorporate mind-body practices from Ayurveda, such as Pranayama (breath control) and mindfulness, to enhance overall wellness.\r\n\r\nAs an integrated cancer care hospital, it will offer several advantages by bringing together diverse medical disciplines and holistic approaches to address the complex needs of cancer patients. \r\n\r\nCosmic healing and naturopathic treatments will also be included in this complementary armamentarium in this integrated cancer care hospital to promote physical, mental, and emotional well-being and outcomes of cancer therapies.. \r\n\r\nAa an integrated cancer care hospital, by combining the strengths of various medical approaches, we will aim to enhance the overall well-being of cancer patients, addressing their physical, emotional, and supportive needs in a holistic manner.\r\n\r\nThe proposed Hospital will be a best-in-class facility and will transform Uttarakhand into a  world-renowned state ( AYUSH destination) to be known for the proposed Cancer Care Hospital run by reputed cancer surgeons who will deliver holistic cancer treatment leveraging strengths of India’s traditional Aurveda sciences. \r\n\r\nThe Proposed Hospital will also go a long way to promote the stated AYUSH Policy,2023 of the Govt of Uttarakhand. The Hospital will enable State of Uttarakhand to deliver on the Hon’ble Prime Minister of India’s vision of building a “New India” which will be a “healthy India”  where its own traditional systems like Ayurveda can play a significant role by providing quality complementary therapies and medical care for its citizens.\r\n\r\nProject Outlay \r\n\r\nCost of Construction , Equipment and other facilities   :      Rs 60 Cr.\r\n\r\nCost of Land ( 7-8 Bighas)                                            :       Rs  7 Cr\r\n\r\nSource of Funds : Personal investment of Promoters for Construction of the facility\r\nEstimated Time :  2 Years from land allotment.\r\n\r\nWe will need about 7 to 8 bighas of suitable land in the vicinity of Dehradun city with good accessibility by roads for patients convenience. \r\n\r\nRequest \r\n\r\nWe will earnestly request and seek help of the Govt of Uttarakhand to  make available and allot  to  us 7-8 bighas suitable of land for setting up the proposed Hospital . \r\n\r\nWe have no doubt that the proposed Hospital will be a shining example in the healthcare map of the State of Uttarakhand and will help  us in making Uttarakhand a medical destination as well.\r\n\r\n\r\nWho we are?\r\n\r\nThe proposed Super Speciality Cancer Care Hospital  is proposed to be established at Dehradun by Dr Kavita Singh together with some other leading medical professionals in cancer treatment supported by accomplished doctors in Ayurvedic sciences and experienced corporate experts. \r\n\r\n Brief background of the team is given below:\r\n\r\nDr Kavita Singh M.B.B.S, M.D., FRCOG\r\n\r\nPresently Consultant Surgical Oncologist, Pan-Birmingham Gynaecological Cancer Centre, Birmingham, Program Director for Subspecialty training, Associate Professor in Cancer Institute University of Birmingham, England , Visiting surgeon- Max Hospital  Dehradun/Delhi and other Hospitals in India. \r\n\r\nDr Kavita Singh is a renowned cancer surgeon with over 30 years of clinical experience of having worked in UK, USA, France, Ethiopia and India. Her clinical and surgical accomplishments in cancer care well known not only in western countries but also in India as she regularly and often visits India as a visiting surgeon for performing surgeries in complex cases in different hospitals across India and to participate in different conferences and teaching forums across India and overseas.\r\n\r\n Dr Kavita frequently operates as a visiting surgeon in, complex cancer cases, at Max Healthcare , Dehradun, Max HealthCare , Saket, New Delhi, Ruby Hospital,Pune, Opollo Hospital, Kolkata, IVY Hospital, Mohali, Chandigarh and Artemis Hospital, Gurgaon. \r\n\r\nShe possesses immense management skills for conducting successful screening , training and teaching programs from Pan-Birmingham Gynaecology cancer centres in England  which is one of the largest and busiest cancer center for women in  England  with best survival figures for ovarian cancers in UK . Having been  affiliated with national cancer societies in India, Dr Kavita  has brought together a team of national and international experts in oncology, who if given an appropriate opportunity are willing to provide their expert services in cancer care delivery in Uttarakhand.\r\n\r\nDr Kavita has established track record of producing very good results in cancer treatment by following an integrated holistic approach to cancer care delivery involving conventional medical treatments in conjunction with alternative treatments like Ayurveda, nutrition and cosmic healing. This is what she proposes to adopt at the proposed Cancer Hospital  to make it unique of its kind in India. \r\n\r\nAn integrated approach to cancer care will be  combining richness and strength of both  western medicine  and traditional Indian science of Ayurveda and is expected to give spectacular results in cancer care outcomes. \r\n\r\nWomen’s cancer care is often not given sufficient emphasis in spite of breast, cervical, lung and bowel cancer are on the rise.  The proposed Cancer Centre will aim to provide focus on prevention, screening, prehabilitation and rehabilitation program. \r\n\r\nDr Kavita now resides, partly, at Village Purkul, Dehradun-248009 and that explains  her determination to give back to the country  and the society by establishing the proposed Cancer Care Centre at Dehradun which hopefully will go a long way to ensure that best-in-class cancer treatment is made available  to cancer patients in Uttarakhand and for rest of the country at the proposed  Super Speciality Cancer Hospital , Dehradun. \r\n\r\n\r\nMr. Ajit Yadav\r\n\r\n\r\nAjit Yadav is an accomplished corporate professional and has been a member of Board of Directors of reputed companies and holds over 30 years of rich and diverse experience. He has played significant role in the management of large and diverse businesses apart from being an experienced professional in the corporate and business law domain both in domestic and international businesses for manufacturing and service sector. \r\n\r\nAjit had been closely connected with healthcare industries since 90s as a senior executive of a leading pharma giant and he has done considerable work in pharmaceutical sector for growth of industry, collaborative clinical research initiatives between private and public sector.\r\n\r\nAjit carries unique experience of combination of private sector together with experience of having served in the IAS (Allied) Services in the Govt of India at an early stage of his professional career. He now sits an Independent Director on the Board of Directors of a reputed business and he is a practicing attorney of the Supreme Court of India. \r\n\r\nSummary \r\n\r\nWith our expertise and determination, we have no doubt that we will establish a Cancer care of repute in the State of Uttarakhand,  \r\n\r\nThe facility will be maintained with very high standards in its aesthetic and clinical conditions. Our  team carries wealth of experience and  is ideally suited to drive this project and offer a best-in-class cancer care hospital in Uttarakhand. \r\n\r\n                                                   --------------------------------------\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', NULL, 700000000,