	(1105, 'C-12/2023/189', 'World Environment Council', NULL, 'Prof Ganesh Channa', 'ganesh.channa@yahoo.com', '9822949285', 'India', 'MEDIUM', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'PROJECT REPORT\r\nFOR\r\nWORLD ENVIRONMENT \r\nUNIVERSITY\r\nPrepared BY\r\nD P SETHI & ASSOCIATES\r\nWORLD ENVIRONMENT COUNCIL\r\nCIN: U85300DL2021NPL384119\r\nNew Delhi', NULL, 250000000, 'Organization', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'C', 'S', NULL, NULL, NULL, 890, 'SUBMITTED', NULL, 'N', 'N', 'Y', '2023-12-04 11:02:28', NULL, 'I', NULL, 890, 'N', 'N', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-12-04 05:32:28', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'N', NULL, NULL, NULL),
	(1106, 'B-12/2023/100', 'AatmaNirbhar Society ', NULL, 'Ranjeet Chaturvedi', 'info@projectaatmanirbhar.org', '9873122970', 'India', 'MEDIUM', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Project Brief (Requirement of Land/Support Required) *\r\n\r\nPROJECT TITLE: Yamuna Valley - Worlds First Herbal Valley \r\n\r\nSYNOPSIS:\r\nUttarakhand, nestled in the Himalayas, serves as a botanical haven, boasting 701 out of 1,748 medicinal plant species found in the Indian Himalayan region. The region\'s diverse ecosystems, spanning from tropical to temperate, create an optimal environment for the flourishing of medicinal plants. Uttarakhand\'s unique landscapes and climate make it an ideal region for cultivating medicinal plants, offering economic benefits to its rural population engaged in agriculture. \r\n\r\nThe initiative, exemplified by “Project Aatmanirbhar Society”, registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (Central Act, 21 of 1860) strategically focuses on the Yamuna Valley basin to harness the therapeutic potential of herbs, aligning with Ayurvedic wisdom and contributing to biodiversity conservation. This endeavor addresses challenges such as subsistence-oriented farming and poor infrastructure, providing a diversified income source. Additionally, it plays a role in environmental restoration, emphasizing the holistic goals of sustainability and promoting indigenous knowledge in line with the "Aatmanirbhar Bharat" initiative. Overall, the project represents a significant step toward leveraging India\'s natural wealth for healthcare and sustainable development.\r\n\r\nOBJECTIVES:\r\nTo Make Herbal Yamuna Valley and Uttarakhand Herbal Valley of the World - Putting the Yamuna Valley and Uttarakhand on the world map as the first herbal Valley of the world. If this model is successful, then it will be repeated it in the 24 other valleys of Uttarakhand to make Uttarakhand, the herbal basket of the world. \r\nWomen Empowerment - A detailed project proposal has been developed and around 1000 women from different villages across Yamunotri valley have been approached for an enrolment in this project. This aspect of engaging women in this project has been purposefully thought to achieve women empowerment in this area.\r\nDecreasing the wild collection of herbs - We aim at developing herbal valley which can be called as “basket of herbs” for the benefit of society. This will alternately help in decreasing the wild collection of herbs, both, legally and illegally.\r\nMigration of villagers - In our developing country, migration of villagers to the cities is a burning issue and such efforts can definitely pave a way for these villagers to engage themselves in such income generating activity. \r\nKnowledge Exchange - Facilitate the exchange of knowledge between local farmers and experts in herb cultivation, blending traditional wisdom with contemporary techniques.\r\nSustainable Practices - Implement sustainable farming methods to ensure environmental preservation and long-term resource availability. \r\nEconomic Empowerment - Generate additional income sources for local farming communities through the cultivation and sale of herbs. \r\nCommunity Cohesion - Foster a sense of unity and collaboration within the community, strengthening social bonds and shared responsibility. \r\nHealth and Wellness -  Promote the use of locally cultivated herbs for medicinal and culinary purposes, improving community health and nutrition.\r\nHerbal Tourism - Organize guided tours showcasing medicinal plants and herbs in the valley. Promote adventure activities like trekking, camping, and wildlife safaris in the valley\'s pristine wilderness. Collaborate with local adventure operators to offer herbal experiences along with outdoor adventures.\r\nHerbal Education Experiences - Offer workshops on herbal medicine preparation guided by local experts. Establish educational centers and museums focusing on valley herbs\' medicinal properties and cultural significance. Provide educational programs on herbalism and traditional healing methods. \r\nCultural Experiences - Highlight local culture, including folk dances, music, and rituals tied to herbal practices. - Encourage interaction with local communities to learn sustainable farming and harvesting techniques. \r\n\r\n\r\nSUPPORT REQUIRED FOR LAND:\r\nUttarkhand Silk Board has provided us information about specific land parcels where nurseries can be built. Sabhawala, Vikas Nagar, Herburtpur, Atuwala, Badripur, Naugaon, and Devdung are the locations on this list that are more accessible and close to Yamunotri Valley. Project Aatmanirbhar would enter into a long-term lease and partnership with Silk Board for such land parcels. \r\n\r\nTop-Tier Nurseries will be developed in this land parcels with integrated facility for the cultivation, processing, and storage of medicinal herbs along-with incorporating sustainable farming, efficient processing, and high-quality storage methods.\r\n\r\nProposed Facilities and Infrastructure to be built on this land parcels for Medicinal Herb Cultivation.\r\nIntercropping practices.\r\nLand development, Fencing and water supply. \r\nNursery-cum-processing Area.\r\nStorage units for harvested herbs.\r\nCleaning facilities including sorting and washing.\r\nHerb drying facility with controlled humidity and temperature.\r\nGrinding facility for processing herbs into powders or other forms.\r\nPacking and labeling system.\r\nIn-house quality testing laboratory.\r\nFinal product storage.\r\nDispatch system for efficient distribution.\r\n\r\nSUPPORT FROM OTHER AGENCIES:\r\nProject Aatmanirbhar Society will require support from all agencies under the Agriculture, Forest, Ayush and Women Welfare departments to access the benefits and schemes available to ensure that all such benefits are able to reach the farmers and women under this programme. \r\n', NULL, 50000000, 'Organization', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'B', 'S', NULL, NULL, NULL, 891, 'SUBMITTED', NULL, 'N', 'N', 'Y', '2023-12-04 12:05:36', NULL, 'I', NULL, 891, 'N', 'N', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2023-12-04 06:35:36', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'N', NULL, NULL, NULL);
